'''Gabriel Teodoro Martinelli Silva''' (Brazilian Portuguese: [[Help:IPA/Portuguese|[ga.bɾiˈɛw maʁ.tʃiˈnɛ.lɪ]]], born 18 June 2001) is a Brazilian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] or left winger for {{English football updater|Arsenal}} club [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]].

Martinelli began his senior career playing for [[Ituano FC|Ituano]] and signed for Arsenal in July 2019 for a reported fee of £6&nbsp;million, where he has won the [[Premier League]], and the [[FA Community Shield]]. He represented Brazil at the [[2020 Summer Olympics]], winning an Olympic Gold in [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|men's football]]. He made his senior debut in 2022 and has played at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and the [[2024 Copa América]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Guarulhos]], São Paulo, Martinelli started his career in 2010, playing for [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]]' [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista (futsal)|futsal team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com.br/noticia/714199_ele-fez-mais-de-200-gols-na-base-do-corinthians-foi-para-o-ituano-e-agora-e-testado-no-united|title=Ele fez mais de 200 gols na base do Corinthians, foi para o Ituano e agora é testado no United|trans-title=He scored more than 200 goals at Corinthians' youth setup, went to Ituano and now is trialled at United|publisher=[[ESPN Brasil]]|language=pt-BR|date=28 July 2017|access-date=4 February 2019|archive-date=24 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190424041811/http://www.espn.com.br/noticia/714199_ele-fez-mais-de-200-gols-na-base-do-corinthians-foi-para-o-ituano-e-agora-e-testado-no-united|url-status=dead}}</ref> After making the breakthrough in football fields, he moved to [[Ituano FC|Ituano]] in 2015, having subsequent trials at [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/sp/tem-esporte/futebol/times/ituano/noticia/quem-e-martinelli-artilheiro-da-copinha-trocou-o-corinthians-pelo-ituano-e-e-monitorado-pelo-barca.ghtml|title=Quem é Martinelli? Artilheiro da Copinha trocou o Corinthians pelo Ituano e é monitorado pelo Barça|trans-title=Who is Martinelli? ''Copinha'' goalscorer changed Corinthians for Ituano and is targeted by ''Barça''|publisher=[[Globo Esporte]]|language=pt-BR|date=11 January 2019|access-date=4 February 2019}}</ref>

On 4 November 2017, Martinelli signed his first professional contract until October 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jornalperiscopio.com.br/site/promessa-galo-gabriel-martinelli-assina-ate-2022/|title=Promessa do Galo, Gabriel Martinelli assina até 2022|trans-title=Prospect of ''Galo'', Gabriel Martinelli signs until 2022|publisher=Jornal Periscópio|language=pt-BR|date=4 November 2017|access-date=4 February 2019}}</ref> He made his professional debut the following 17 March, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for goalscorer [[Claudinho (footballer, born 1991)|Claudinho]] in a 2–1 [[Campeonato Paulista]] away win against [[Esporte Clube São Bento|São Bento]]; at the age of 16 years and nine months, he became the youngest player to play for the club in the century.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ituanofc.com/gabriel-martinelli-e-o-atleta-mais-jovem-a-estrear-no-ituano/|title=Gabriel Martinelli é o atleta mais jovem a estrear no Ituano|trans-title=Gabriel Martinelli is the youngest player to debut at Ituano|publisher=Ituano FC|language=pt-BR|date=20 March 2018|access-date=4 February 2019|archive-date=3 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703172917/https://www.ituanofc.com/gabriel-martinelli-e-o-atleta-mais-jovem-a-estrear-no-ituano/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Martinelli scored his first senior goal on 8 September 2018, netting the second in a 4–1 win over [[Clube Atlético Taboão da Serra|Taboão da Serra]], for the year's [[Copa Paulista]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.futebolinterior.com.br/futebol/Copa-Paulista/Unica/2018/noticias/2018-09/ituano-atropela-taboao-da-serra-e-assume-lideranca-na-copa-paulista|title=Taboão da Serra 1&nbsp;×&nbsp;4 Ituano – Com início avassalador, Galo vence e assume liderança|trans-title=Taboão da Serra 1–4 Ituano – With a storming start, ''Galo'' win and take on leadership|publisher=Futebol Interior|language=pt-BR|date=8 September 2014|access-date=4 February 2019}}</ref> Definitively promoted to the first team for the [[2019 Campeonato Paulista]], he scored six goals during the competition, being the club's top goalscorer as they reached the quarterfinals; highlights included a brace in a 3–0 away win against [[Clube Atlético Bragantino|Bragantino]] on 15 March 2019.

===Arsenal===
====2019–2020: Debut season and FA Cup win====
[[File:Gabriel Martinelli 2020.jpg|thumb|upright|Martinelli playing for [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in 2020]]

Martinelli was reportedly subject to interest from a number of clubs but signed a long-term contract with [[Premier League]] club [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on 2 July 2019, for a reported fee of £6&nbsp;million ([[Brazilian real|R$]]46.9&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-martinelli-join-club |title=Gabriel Martinelli to join club |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |date=2 July 2019}}</ref> Holding an [[Italian passport]], Martinelli was not subject to the [[Work permit (United Kingdom)|scrutinised criteria]] required for English clubs to sign South American players.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://tribuna.com/en/arsenal/news/3546797/|title=Gabriel Martinelli does not rule out he could play for Italy|website=[[Tribuna.com]]|access-date=22 January 2020|archive-date=23 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123114115/https://tribuna.com/en/arsenal/news/3546797/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He travelled with the Arsenal first team to their pre-season tour in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rosser |first=Jack |date=11 July 2019 |title=Arsenal confirm pre-season tour squad with Koscielny missing |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/arsenal/arsenal-confirm-2019-preseason-tour-squad-laurent-koscielny-missing-a4187796.html |access-date=21 June 2022 |website=Evening Standard |language=en}}</ref> He scored a goal on his non-competitive debut, in a 3–0 pre-season win against [[Colorado Rapids]] on 16 July.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49000746 |title=Gabriel Martinelli scores as youthful Arsenal team open US tour with win |website=BBC Sport |date=16 July 2019}}</ref> Upon signing, Martinelli was originally set to play primarily with the [[Arsenal F.C. Under-21s and Academy|under-21s]] in his first season, then slowly be integrated from the academy setup to the first-team; however, Martinelli's impressive pre-season and quality in training encouraged Arsenal that he would be ready for immediate first-team integration.<ref>{{Citation |last=Watts |first=Charles |title=Arsenal transfer talk – Released list confirmed, Nketiah's contract, Marquinhos imminent and Lopez |date=10 June 2022 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tg7z5vJZul8&t=393s |language=en |access-date=21 June 2022}}</ref>

Martinelli made his Premier League debut on 11 August 2019 in a 1–0 win against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]], coming on in the 84th minute as a substitute for [[Henrikh Mkhitaryan]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Chowdhury |first=Saj |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49223797 |title=Newcastle 0–1 Arsenal: Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang strike seals win |website=BBC Sport |date=11 August 2019}}</ref> On 24 September, Martinelli scored a brace in his first competitive start for the club in a 5–0 victory over [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in the [[EFL Cup]]. His performance received praise from head coach [[Unai Emery]], who said: "He's hungry to have that opportunity to help us, he is very humble, he fights. I told him to have some patience for his opportunity to do like he was doing. He did that. He deserved it".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49723455 |title=Arsenal 5–0 Nottingham Forest: Unai Emery praises Gabriel Martinelli after League Cup brace |website=BBC Sport |date=24 September 2019}}</ref>

Martinelli made his second start for Arsenal in a 4–0 home win over [[Standard Liège]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]] on 4 October, in which he scored another brace.<ref>{{cite news|last=Sanders |first=Emma |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49874359 |title=Arsenal 4–0 Standard Liege: Gabriel Martinelli impresses in ruthless win |work=BBC Sport |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> Martinelli kept up his goal scoring form, netting the equaliser in a 3–2 home win over [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória Guimarães]] on 24 October, with another header.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50159121|title=Substitute Nicolas Pepe rescued Arsenal with two sublime free-kicks in the last 10 minutes of their Europa League group game against Vitoria Guimaraes at Emirates Stadium|website=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Sanders|date=24 October 2019}}</ref> In the League Cup fourth round on 30 October, Martinelli registered another brace in a 5–5 draw with [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], and also scored his penalty in the penalty shootout, which Arsenal eventually lost.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50148250|title=Liverpool beat Arsenal on penalties to secure their place in the quarter-finals of the Carabao Cup after 10 goals were scored in a thrilling contest at Anfield|website=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Sanders|date=30 October 2019}}</ref> As a result, he became the first player to score four times in his first four starts since [[Ian Wright]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://talksport.com/football/622882/gabriel-martinelli-incredible-arsenal-liverpool/|title=Gabriel Martinelli: Incredible stat emerges as Arsenal teenager nets seventh goal for Gunners against Liverpool|publisher=Talk Sport|date=30 October 2019|first=Oliver|last=Dawnay}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/arsenal/arsenal-four-things-we-learned-mesut-ozil-gabriel-martinelli-impress-liverpool-a4274866.html|title=Liverpool 5–5 Arsenal: Four things we learned as Mesut Ozil and Gabriel Martinelli impress|work=The Standard|first=James|last=Olley|date=30 October 2019}}</ref> Martinelli's performance received praise from Liverpool manager [[Jürgen Klopp]], who labelled him "[the] talent of the century".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tribuna.com/en/arsenal/news/3501752/|title=Jurgen Klopp waxes lyrical about Gabriel Martinelli: 'He came from wherever and is really unbelievable!'|website=Tribuna.com|access-date=30 December 2020|archive-date=23 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123114050/https://tribuna.com/en/arsenal/news/3501752/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Martinelli's performances led to him being awarded the Arsenal 'Player of the Month' award for October, receiving 75% of the total votes cast, beating out [[Mattéo Guendouzi]] and [[Nicolas Pépé]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/martinelli-our-october-player-month|title= Martinelli is our October Player of the Month|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=8 November 2019}}</ref> After the appointment of interim head coach [[Freddie Ljungberg]], Martinelli started his first Premier League game, scoring Arsenal's equaliser in an eventual 1–3 win over [[West Ham United]] on 9 December. On 21 January 2020, Martinelli scored in a 2–2 away draw at [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], making him the first teenager to reach double figures in a season for Arsenal since [[Nicolas Anelka]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51101529|title=Arsenal showed the "togetherness and leadership" that Mikel Arteta is demanding as they overcame David Luiz's red card to fight back twice and share the spoils in an eventful London derby|website=BBC Sport|first=Neil|last=Johnston|date=22 January 2020}}</ref> Picking the ball up outside the Arsenal box following a headed clearance from a corner, Martinelli ran the length of the pitch outpacing Chelsea defenders to slot past Kepa Arrizabalaga. The goal was later voted as Arsenal's Goal of the Season by the club's fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/martinelli-wins-201920-goal-season|title= Martinelli wins 2019/20 Goal of the Season|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=18 August 2020}}</ref> On 3 July, Martinelli signed a new four-year contract, with a team option for an extra year, until 2025.<ref>{{cite web |last=Benge |first=James |date=3 July 2020 |title=James Benge on Twitter: "Gabriel Martinelli's contract is a four-year deal with a club option to extend it". |url=https://twitter.com/jamesbenge/status/1279105933990416385 |via=Twitter}}</ref>{{Primary source inline|date=June 2025}} Shortly after, Martinelli was ruled out until the end of 2020, undergoing surgery to repair a lesion in the cartilage of his knee following an injury in training on 21 June.<ref>{{cite web |date=3 July 2020 |title=Martinelli signs new long-term contract |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/martinelli-signs-new-long-term-contract |publisher=Arsenal F.C.}}</ref>

====2020–2022: Return to fitness, position change and individual success====
Martinelli made his return on 19 December, coming off the bench to play 19 minutes in a 2–1 away defeat to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55268094|title=Eighth Premier League defeat for Gunners this season|first=Phil|last=McNulty|website=BBC Sport|date=19 December 2020}}</ref> During the warmup against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] in the [[FA Cup]] on 9 January 2021, he sustained a minor ankle injury and was replaced in the line-up by [[Reiss Nelson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://talksport.com/football/fa-cup/815232/arsenal-gabriel-martinelli-injury-warm-up-fa-cup-arteta-warning/|title=Mikel Arteta has revealed Gabriel Martinelli was 'in tears' after sustaining a worrying injury in the warm-up ahead of Arsenal's FA Cup tie on Saturday|publisher=Talk Sport|access-date=10 January 2020}}</ref> Martinelli returned to playing in European competition on 18 February, making a 13-minute cameo appearance off the bench in a 1–1 draw against [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56103089|title=Bukayo Saka warned his Arsenal team-mates that they cannot put a foot wrong when they face Benfica in the second leg of their Europa League last-32 tie after his goal earned them a draw in the first game in Rome|work=BBC Sport|first=Phil|last=Dawkes|date=18 February 2021}}</ref> He scored his first goal of the season in a 3–0 away victory against [[Sheffield United]] on 11 April.<ref>{{cite web |date=11 April 2021 |title=Gabriel Martinelli scored in his first start since January as Arsenal ended a run of four games without a win with victory over the Premier League's bottom club Sheffield United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56629081 |work=BBC Sport}}</ref> While previously playing in central positions akin to a [[Forward (association football)|classic number 9]], under [[Mikel Arteta]]'s tutelage, Martinelli was moulded to play more on the left-wing where he had more purchase to cut onto his strong right foot & use his rapid dribbling to unnerve defenders.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Krishnan |first=Joe |date=18 April 2022 |title=Arsenal ace Martinelli can be the answer to Arteta's top-four problems |url=https://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/1597202/Arsenal-Gabriel-Martinelli-Mikel-Arteta-top-four-Premier-League-SNT |access-date=2023-08-21 |website=Daily Express |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=11 April 2021 |title=Gabriel Martinelli could be the perfect Mikel Arteta forward in Arsenal rebuild |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/premier-league/2020-2021/gabriel-martinelli-could-be-the-perfect-mikel-arteta-forward-in-arsenal-rebuild_sto8219591/story.shtml |access-date=2023-08-21 |website=Eurosport |language=en}}</ref>

Martinelli missed pre-season after being selected on international duty in [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament – Final|Brazil's winning Olympic Gold campaign]]. Martinelli scored his first goal (a [[Volley (association football)|volley]] with his second touch of the game) of the [[2021–22 Arsenal F.C. season|2021–22 season]] against Newcastle United on 27 November.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59356976|title=Arsenal eventually broke Newcastle United down to leave Eddie Howe's side bottom of the Premier League without a win|work=BBC Sport|date=27 November 2021|first=Emlyn|last=Begley}}</ref> This goal of his was eventually ranked 3rd in the official Goal of the Season poll held by the club at the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=🏆 2021/22 Goal of the Season: The winner is… |url=https://www.arsenal.com/premier-league-goal-of-the-season-vote-winner-granit-xhaka-manchester-united |access-date=18 June 2022 |website=🏆 2021/22 Goal of the Season: The winner is… |language=en}}</ref> On 18 December, he scored twice against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] three days later, marking his first Premier League brace,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59618480|title=Two goals from Gabriel Martinelli helped Arsenal sweep past an injury-hit Leeds at Elland Road|first=Thomas|last=Mallows|date=18 December 2021|work=BBC Sport}}</ref> with his first goal marking Arsenal's 7,000th scored in top-division English football.<ref>{{cite web|title=Match report: Leeds 1–4 Arsenal|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2021-Dec-18/leeds-1-4-arsenal-match-report|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|first=Josh|last=James|date=18 December 2021|access-date=23 December 2021 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Analysis: Our 7,000 top-flight goals|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/analysis-our-7000-top-flight-goals|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|first=Josh|last=James|date=20 December 2021|access-date=23 December 2021}}</ref> On 10 February 2022, Martinelli was sent off for two yellow cards in the space of four seconds against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolves]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/1564235/Arsenal-s-Gabriel-Martinelli-sent-off-for-two-yellow-cards-in-thirty-seconds-vs-Wolves |title=Martinelli sent off |work=Daily Express |date=11 February 2022}}</ref> It was his first red card in his career. The red card gained some controversy as he was given two yellow cards in one passage of play, starting with pushing [[Daniel Podence]] after a throw in and then a foul against [[Nélson Semedo]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 February 2022 |title=Rio Ferdinand didn't hold back when asked for his opinion on Martinelli's crazy red card v Wolves |url=https://www.givemesport.com/87971567-martinelli-red-card-rio-ferdinand-was-not-happy-with-decision-to-send-off-arsenal-star |access-date=15 April 2022 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

Before the conclusion of the 2021–22 season, Martinelli was handed the number 11 shirt pending the departure of [[Lucas Torreira]] to [[Galatasaray S.K.|Galatasaray]] in the summer transfer window.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Deniran-Alleyne |first=Tashan |date=20 May 2022 |title=Gabriel Martinelli not permitted to wear Arsenal number 11 shirt against Everton |url=https://www.football.london/arsenal-fc/news/martinelli-arsenal-shirt-everton-ronaldo-24007812 |access-date=2023-08-21 |website=Football.London |language=en}}</ref> His former number 35 was later taken up by [[Oleksandr Zinchenko (footballer)|Oleksandr Zinchenko]] upon the latter's arrival.

====2022–present: Joint-top scorer, title challengers====
[[File:2023 MLS All Star Game 2023-07-19 Gabriel Martinelli.jpg|thumb|Martinelli playing for [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[2023 MLS All-Star Game]]]]

On 5 August 2022, Martinelli scored for Arsenal in their 2–0 away win at [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], becoming the first Brazilian to net a season-opening goal of a Premier League campaign.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/2722348 |title=Martinelli makes history with opening goal |date=5 August 2022 |publisher=Premier League |access-date=6 August 2022 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/2713932 |title=Friday review: Arsenal open with a hard-fought win |date=5 August 2022 |publisher=Premier League |access-date=6 August 2022 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/three-things-we-noticed-against-palace |title=Three things we noticed against Palace |last=James |first=Josh |date=5 August 2022 |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |access-date=6 August 2022 }}</ref> On 31 August, Martinelli scored a 77th minute winner in a home match against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], which gave Arsenal five wins from their opening five matches of the season.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Arsenal maintain their 100% start against Villa |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62655351 |access-date=2023-08-10}}</ref> On 1 October, Martinelli provided an assist for [[Granit Xhaka]] in Arsenal's 3–1 victory over North London rivals [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Arsenal beat 10-man Tottenham to go four clear |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63017880 |access-date=2023-08-10}}</ref> One week later on 9 October, he opened the scoring within 58 seconds in Arsenal's home match against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], which the Gunners would go on to win 3–2, and was awarded [[Player of the match|Man of the Match]] for his display.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Saka double as Arsenal beat Liverpool to go top |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63106170 |access-date=2023-08-10}}</ref> On [[Boxing Day]], Martinelli scored in Arsenal's first Premier League match since the conclusion of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], a 3–1 win over [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Arsenal fight back to extend Premier League lead |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64022710 |access-date=2023-08-10}}</ref>

On 3 February 2023, Martinelli signed a new long-term contract with the club, tying him down until 2027.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/gabriel-martinelli-signs-new-long-term-contract |title=Gabriel Martinelli signs new long-term contract |date=3 February 2023 |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |access-date=3 February 2023 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12801759/gabriel-martinelli-arsenal-forward-signs-new-contract-with-premier-league-leaders-until-2027 |title=Gabriel Martinelli: Arsenal forward signs new contract with Premier League leaders until 2027 |date=3 February 2023 |publisher=Sky Sports News |access-date=3 February 2023 }}</ref> On 25 February, Martinelli scored the only goal of the game in an away win over [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Martinelli gives Arsenal narrow win at Leicester |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64686324 |access-date=2023-08-10}}</ref> In Arsenal's next match against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] on 1 March, Martinelli netted a brace as Arsenal ran out 4–0 winners and moved five points clear at the top of the Premier League table.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Arsenal rout Everton to go five points clear at top |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62784289 |access-date=2023-08-10}}</ref> By the end of the [[2022–23 Arsenal F.C. season|season]], Martinelli had scored 15 goals and provided 6 assists in all competitions, becoming the club's joint-top scorer for the season alongside [[Martin Ødegaard]], and finished third in [[Arsenal Player of the Season|Arsenal's Player of the Season]] vote.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 August 2023 |title=Player of the Season: Martinelli finishes third |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/player-season-gabriel-martinelli-finishes-third |access-date=2023-08-10 |website=Player of the Season: Martinelli finishes third |language=en}}</ref> Martinelli also became the highest scoring Brazilian player in a single Premier League season, equalling [[Roberto Firmino]]'s record for [[2017–18 Liverpool F.C. season|Liverpool in the 2017–18 season]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Gabriel Martinelli ties EPL record for goals scored by Brazilians – Futbol on FanNation |language=en |work=Futbol on FanNation |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/news/gabriel-martinelli-ties-epl-record-for-goals-scored-by-brazilians |access-date=2023-08-21}}</ref>

On 12 August 2023, in Arsenal's first match of the [[2023–24 Premier League|2023–24 Premier League season]], Martinelli assisted [[Eddie Nketiah]] by pirouetting past [[Serge Aurier]] & [[Danilo (footballer, born 2001)|Danilo Oliveira]] in a 2–1 home win against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]].<ref>{{Citation |title=HIGHLIGHTS {{!}} Arsenal vs Nottingham Forest (2–1) {{!}} Premier League {{!}} Nketiah, Saka | date=12 August 2023 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xMrC3TE3rtE |access-date=2023-08-21 |language=en}}</ref> On 3 September, Martinelli provided the assist for Martin Ødegaard's equaliser against Manchester United, just 35 seconds after going 1–0 down. Arsenal would later seal a 3–1 victory.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hytner |first=David |date=3 September 2023 |title=Declan Rice late strike earns Arsenal dramatic Manchester United victory |language=en-GB |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/sep/03/arsenal-manchester-united-premier-league-match-report |access-date=2023-09-25 |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 8 October, Martinelli came on as a substitute and scored the only goal of the game in a 1–0 victory over [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] with the help of a deflection off defender [[Nathan Aké]], as Arsenal sealed their first league win against their opponents since 2015.<ref>{{cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66974882 |title=Arsenal 1–0 Manchester City |work=BBC Sport |date=8 October 2023 }}</ref> On 24 October, he made his [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut, in which he scored the first goal in a 2–1 away win against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/champions-league/2023-2024/round-up-harry-kane-on-target-as-bayern-munich-maintain-perfect-champions-league-start-inter-win-at-_sto9850410/story.shtml |title=Gabriel Martinelli scores on Champions League debut as Arsenal triumph, Harry Maguire on target as Manchester United win |publisher=Eurosport |date=24 October 2023 }}</ref> On 4 February 2024, Martinelli scored as Arsenal defeated Liverpool 3–1, taking advantage of an error from Liverpool’s defense.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68120819 |title=Arsenal 3–1 Liverpool: Gunners move within two points of Premier League leaders |author=Phil McNulty |date=4 February 2025 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=20 September 2025}}</ref>

On 10 November 2024, Martinelli scored the opening goal as Arsenal drew 1–1 with [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/704380/arsenal-chelsea |title=Arsenal 1–0 Chelsea: Gunners edge past Blues to revive title hopes |website=ESPN UK |date=16 March 2025 |access-date=20 September 2025}}</ref> On 16 April 2025, in the second leg of the UEFA Champions League quarter-finals, Martinelli scored a late winner as Arsenal defeated [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] 2–1 at the [[Santiago Bernabéu Stadium|Santiago Bernabéu]], securing a 5–1 aggregate victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2044855--real-madrid-vs-arsenal/ |title=Real Madrid 1–2 Arsenal (1–5 agg): Gunners oust holders to advance |website=UEFA.com |date=16 April 2025 |access-date=20 September 2025}}</ref> On 11 May 2025, he scored a header at [[Anfield]] to help Arsenal come back from 2–0 down, with the match ending 2–2 against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2025-May-11/liverpool-2-2-arsenal-match-report |title=Report: Liverpool 2–2 Arsenal |website=Arsenal.com |date=11 May 2025 |access-date=20 September 2025}}</ref>

Despite Arsenal signing new attacking additions before the [[2025–26 Premier League|2025–26 Premier League season]], including [[Noni Madueke]] and [[Eberechi Eze]], Martinelli enjoyed a resurgence in his new role.<ref>{{cite web |title=Martinelli's 'controlled anger' shows why he is important to Arsenal |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c1477yx5d37o |website=BBC Sport |access-date=21 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Martinelli 'hungry to prove himself' |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cd63pdl5w37o |website=BBC Sport |access-date=2 October 2025}}</ref> On 21 September, he came off the bench to score a late equaliser in a 1–1 Premier League draw against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Arsenal 1–1 Manchester City |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2025-Sep-21/arsenal-1-1-manchester-city-match-report |website=Arsenal.com |access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref> On 21 October, he scored against [[Atlético Madrid]] in a 4–0 Champions League win.<ref>{{cite web |title=Arsenal vs Atlético Madrid – Match preview & news |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2025-Oct-21/atletico-madrid#!match-news |website=Arsenal.com |access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref> On 26 November, Martinelli scored in a 3–1 Champions League win over [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Arsenal 3–1 Bayern Munich |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2025-Nov-26/arsenal-3-1-bayern-munich-match-report |website=Arsenal.com |access-date=27 November 2025}}</ref> By scoring in a 3–0 away victory against [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] in the Champions League on 10 December, Martinelli became the first Arsenal player to score in 5 consecutive Champions League matches.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-01-03 |title=Martinelli breaks Champions League goals record |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/martinelli-breaks-champions-league-goals-record |access-date=2026-01-02 |website=Martinelli breaks Champions League goals record |language=en}}</ref> On 11 January 2026, Martinelli scored the first [[hat-trick]] of his career in a 4–1 [[2025–26 FA Cup|FA Cup]] win at [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/arsenal-player-ratings-hat-trick-hero-gabriel-martinelli-gets-gunners-into-fa-cup-fourth-round/bltad868f05c64a19ef|title=Arsenal player ratings vs Portsmouth: Hat-trick hero Gabriel Martinelli fires Gunners into FA Cup fourth round as 'Set-Piece FC' flex their muscles to survive early scare &#124; Goal.com US|date=11 January 2026|website=www.goal.com}}</ref>

==International career==
Martinelli was born in Brazil, and is of Italian descent through his father;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/cybrown/2019/07/02/5-things-to-know-about-new-arsenal-attacker-gabriel-martinelli/|title=5 Things To Know About New Arsenal Attacker Gabriel Martinelli|first=Cy|last=Brown|website=Forbes}}</ref> he holds dual [[Brazilian-Italian]] citizenship.<ref name=":0" /> On 20 May 2019, Martinelli was called up by [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]] manager [[Tite (football manager)|Tite]] to complete preparatory training for the [[2019 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/sp/tem-esporte/futebol/times/ituano/noticia/martinelli-do-ituano-e-chamado-por-tite-para-treinos-da-selecao-na-copa-america.ghtml|title=Martinelli, do Ituano, é chamado por Tite para treinos da Seleção na Copa América|trans-title=Martinelli, from Ituano, is called up by Tite for trainings of the ''Seleção'' in the Copa América|publisher=Globo Esporte|language=pt-BR|date=20 May 2019|access-date=4 June 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, Martinelli appeared for [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil's under-23 side]] at the United International Football Festival in Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-base-masculina/selecao-brasileira-olimpica-definida-para-encarar-os-eua-na-espanha|title=Seleção Brasileira Olímpica definida para encarar os EUA na Espanha|trans-title=Olympic Brazil squad set to face the USA in Spain|publisher=[[Brazilian Football Confederation]]|language=pt-BR|date=14 November 2019|access-date=14 November 2019}}</ref>

On 2 July 2021, Martinelli was named in the [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil]] squad for the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2020 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Com mudanças, Jardine anuncia os 22 convocados para defender o Brasil nas Olimpíadas de Tóquio |url=https://ge.globo.com/olimpiadas/noticia/noticias-selecao-olimpica-22-jogadores-convocados-toquio-japao-jardine.ghtml |publisher=Globo Esporte |access-date=2 July 2021 |date=2 July 2021 }}</ref> On 3 August, Martinelli scored Brazil's second penalty to help defeat [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico]] in the Olympic semi-final, before becoming a gold medallist after Brazil defeated [[Spain national under-23 football team|Spain]] in the final four days later.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58129614|title=Brazil defended their Olympic men's football title following a dramatic extra-time victory over Spain|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=8 August 2021}}</ref> He was named in the 25-man [[Brazil national football team|senior Brazil squad]] on 11 March 2022 for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] and [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{Cite web |author1=Greg Lea Contributions from Conor Pope |date=24 March 2022 |title=Brazil World Cup 2022 squad: Tite names his final qualification squad |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/brazil-world-cup-2022-squad-players-qatar-line-up |access-date=28 March 2022 |website=fourfourtwo.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Arsenal star Martinelli receives first Brazil call-up as Neymar returns for upcoming 2022 World Cup qualifiers {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en-om/news/arsenal-martinelli-first-brazil-call-up-neymar-returns-2022/bltc0478cfa914f83b2 |access-date=28 March 2022 |website=Goal (website)}}</ref> Martinelli made his international debut when he came off the bench for [[Vinícius Júnior]] in Brazil's 4–0 win over Chile at the [[Maracanã Stadium|Maracana Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Internationals: Pepe, Tierney and Odegaard score |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/internationals-pepe-tierney-and-odegaard-score |access-date=28 March 2022 |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Brazil vs. Chile – Football Match Summary – 24 March, 2022 – ESPN |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/561015 |access-date=28 March 2022 |publisher=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

On 7 November 2022, Martinelli was named in the squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Seleção Brasileira está convocada para a Copa do Mundo FIFA Qatar 2022|url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/selecao-brasileira-esta-convocada-para-a-copa-do-mundo-fifa-qatar-2022|publisher=[[Brazilian Football Confederation|CBF]]|access-date=7 November 2022|date=7 November 2022|language=pt}}</ref> making his World Cup debut coming on as a substitute for [[Raphinha]] in the 87th minute of Brazil's opening 2–0 victory against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Brazil vs. Serbia −24 November 2022 – Soccerway |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2022/11/24/world/world-cup/brazil/serbia/3749537/ |publisher=Soccerway |access-date=7 July 2023}}</ref> Martinelli would be an unused substitute in Brazil's 1–0 victory over [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Brazil vs. Switzerland −28 November 2022 – Soccerway|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2022/11/28/world/world-cup/brazil/switzerland/3749539/|publisher=Soccerway|access-date=7 July 2023}}</ref> and would play the full match in Brazil's 1–0 defeat to [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Cameroon vs. Brazil −2 December 2022 – Soccerway |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2022/12/02/world/world-cup/cameroon/brazil/3749541/ |publisher=Soccerway |access-date=7 July 2023}}</ref> Martinelli was involved in Brazil's 4–1 victory over [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] in the round of 16, coming on as a substitute for [[Vinícius Júnior]] in the 72nd minute,<ref>{{cite web|title=Brazil vs. Korea Republic – 5 December 2022 – Soccerway|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2022/12/05/world/world-cup/brazil/korea-republic/3298979/|publisher=Soccerway|access-date=7 July 2023}}</ref> and was an unused substitute in Brazil's quarter-final match against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], which Brazil would lose 4–2 on penalties after a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web|title=Croatia vs. Brazil – 9 December 2022 – Soccerway|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2022/12/09/world/world-cup/croatia/brazil/3298983/|publisher=Soccerway|access-date=7 July 2023}}</ref>

On 16 November 2023, Martinelli scored his first goal for Brazil in a 2–1 defeat against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] in [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Colombia vs. Brazil 2 – 1|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2023/11/17/south-america/wc-qualifying-south-america/colombia/brazil/4191287/|publisher=Soccerway|access-date=17 November 2023}}</ref> Martinelli scored his second international goal in a 2–3 away victory in a [[2024 Copa América]] pre-tournament preparation match against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] at [[Kyle Field]] on 8 June 2024.<ref>{{cite web|title=Endrick heads late Brazil winner to deny Mexico comeback|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/692533|publisher=ESPN|access-date=9 June 2024}}</ref> On 14 October 2025, he scored his third Brazil goal in a 3–2 friendly away loss against [[Japan national football team|Japan]] in Tokyo.<ref>{{cite web|title=Japan completed a superb second-half turnaround to secure a first-ever victory over Brazil in their international friendly in Tokyo|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c3w5gn16l6nt|publisher=BBC|access-date=15 October 2025}}</ref> On 31 March 2026, Martinelli scored his fourth international goal in a friendly against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], scoring Brazil's third in a 3–1 victory at [[Camping World Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Brazil score twice late on to beat Croatia 3-1 in World Cup tune-up|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/matchstats/_/gameId/401843261|publisher=ESPN|access-date=1 April 2026}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Martinelli often plays as a dynamic and explosive wide forward, and is known for his acceleration, speed and defensive intensity.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Martinelli's 'all-round game exceptional' – Arsenal boss Arteta |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/c72lky4pvdeo |access-date=1 July 2022 |website=BBC Sport |date=11 March 2022 |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=pmanalytics |date=5 August 2020 |title=Gabriel Martinelli – Player Analysis |url=https://pmanalytics.wordpress.com/2020/08/05/gabriel-martinelli-player-analysis/ |access-date=1 July 2022 |website=PM Analytics |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Bil |first1=Toni |last2=zic |title=Gabriel Martinelli: A spark of hope for Arsenal |url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/article/gabriel-martinelli-scout-report-tactical-analysis-tactics |access-date=1 July 2022 |website=Total Football Analysis Magazine |date=19 January 2021 |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Martinelli is in a relationship with Isabella Rousso.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Chakraborty |first=Sushan |date=8 May 2023 |title=Arsenal attacker's girlfriend hails his brilliant performance in 2–0 win over Newcastle in her Instagram story |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/news-arsenal-attacker-s-girlfriend-makes-brilliant-instagram-claim-2-0-win-newcastle |access-date=2023-10-12 |website=sportskeeda.com |language=en-gb}}</ref> In March 2025, they announced their engagement.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sharan |first=Meghna |date=2025-03-27 |title=💍 She said yes! Gabriel Martinelli proposes to his long-term girlfriend Isabella |url=https://tribuna.com/en/blogs/she-said-yes-gabriel-martinelli-proposes-to-his-longterm-gir/ |access-date=2025-07-11 |website=Tribuna.com}}</ref>

